behavior wash_fork(fork:item, sink:item):
    body:
        achieve close_char(char, fork)
        # Ensure the character is close to the fork

        achieve_once inside(fork, sink)
        # Ensure the fork is placed inside the sink for washing

        wash(fork)
        # Wash the fork

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind fork1: item where:
            is_fork(fork1) and id[fork1]==2080
        # Select fork with ID 2080
        
        bind fork2: item where:
            is_fork(fork2) and id[fork2]==2081
        # Select fork with ID 2081
        
        bind sink: item where:
            is_sink(sink)
        # Select a sink
        
        wash_fork(fork1, sink)
        wash_fork(fork2, sink)

behavior wash_fork(fork:item):
    body:
        achieve dirty(fork)
        # Ensure the fork is dirty before proceeding to wash it
        achieve clean(fork)
        # The goal is to have the fork cleaned

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        foreach fork: item:
            if is_fork(fork) and dirty(fork):
                # Check all dirty forks to wash them by hand
                wash_fork(fork)

behavior wash_fork(fork: item, sink: item):
    body:
        achieve inside(fork, sink)
        # Ensure the fork is placed inside the sink

        achieve dirty(fork) 
        # The fork needs to be washed because it is currently dirty

        wash(fork) 
        # Wash the fork by hand

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind table: item where:
            is_table(table) and id[table] == 226
        # Select table with ID 226

        bind fork1: item where:
            is_fork(fork1) and on(fork1, table)
        # Select the first fork on the table

        bind fork2: item where:
            is_fork(fork2) and on(fork2, table)
        # Select the second fork on the table

        bind sink: item where:
            is_sink(sink) and id[sink] == 231
        # Select a sink with ID 231

        wash_fork(fork1, sink)
        wash_fork(fork2, sink)
        # Wash both forks by hand using the sink

behavior clean_fork(fork:item, sink:item):
    body:
        achieve_once inhand(fork)
        achieve inside(fork, sink)
        wash(fork)
        achieve clean(fork)

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        foreach fork: item:
            if is_fork(fork) and dirty(fork):
                bind sink: item where:
                    is_sink(sink)
                # Ensure fork is washed and cleaned
                clean_fork(fork, sink)
